<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego man died early Tuesday of gunshot wounds he received the night 
before. 
</P>
<P>
Francisco Sanchez-Chaires, 32, was found in the 3600 block of Van Dyke Avenue 
in East San Diego by police shortly after 10 p.m. Monday. He was taken to Mercy 
Hospital and died at 1:50 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
A deputy county coroner said Sanches-Chaires was shot in the upper right arm 
and chest. He was a gardener and lived in the 3000 block of 40th Street. 
</P>
</TEXT>
