<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DIES WHEN WOMAN STEPS ON GAS BY MISTAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year old North Hollywood man was killed Tuesday morning while sitting in 
front of a convenience store when a young woman accidentally hit the 
accelerator instead of the brake pedal while trying to park her car, Los 
Angeles police reported. 
</P>
<P>
Roman Gudino was killed as he sat in front of the Lankershim Boulevard store 
with a cold drink, Officer Bill Mulvihill said. 
</P>
<P>
Mulvihill said the driver, Eva Hernandez Olivo, 22, of Sun Valley was 
attempting to park in the store's lot when she hit the gas pedal and her car 
struck Gudino. 
</P>
<P>
Olivo fled but was arrested later after her husband notified police of her 
involvement in the accident, Mulvihill said. 
</P>
<P>
Olivo was arrested on suspicion of felony hit-and-run, the officer reported. 
</P>
