<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: ENCINO'S GREENWOOD WINS U.S. OPEN QUALIFYING EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Richard Greenwood of Encino led all players with an even-par 144 for 36 holes 
in a U. S. Open qualifying tournament held Monday and Tuesday at Industry 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Greenwood fired rounds of 74 and 70 and was one of 15 players in the 182-man 
field to advance to the sectional tournament next month. 
</P>
<P>
Wayne Case of Thousand Oaks, who shot 75-74 -- 149, also advanced. Craig 
Steinberg, an amateur from Van Nuys, advanced at 72-78 -- 150. The sectional 
qualifying tournament is June 5 at San Francisco Golf Course. The U. S. Open is 
June 14-17 at Medinah Country Club in Medinah, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
Heavyweight John Bray of Van Nuys was among 48 boxers named by the U. S. 
Amateur Boxing Federation to compete for one of 24 berths on the U. S. boxing 
team for the Goodwill Games. 
</P>
<P>
Bray will fight either June 8 or June 9 in the Goodwill Games Boxing Challenge 
at the Mirage Hotel in Las Vegas. A win would qualify Bray for the Goodwill 
Games; a loss would send him to the U. S. Olympic Festival. 
</P>
<P>
Mara Phillips, a shortstop at Chatsworth High, has signed a letter of intent to 
play softball at Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
Phillips, who has led the Chancellors to the City Section 4-A Division 
semifinals, is batting .446. 
</P>
<P>
The Southern Section softball playoff game between Simi Valley and Mater Dei 
has been rescheduled for today at 3 p.m. at Rancho Simi Community Park. The 
quarterfinal-round game originally was scheduled for Thursday but was moved at 
the request of Mater Dei because of a conflict with the school prom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
