<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
KENNEDY POSTS TENNIS VICTORY OVER VAN NUYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There are no standouts on Kennedy High's standout tennis team. Coach Craig Raub 
says balance is his team's strength, and Kennedy proved it in a 22-7 1/2 win 
over Van Nuys in the City Section 3-A Division playoff semifinals Tuesday at 
the Racquet Centre in Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
Every Kennedy singles player won at least one match, and the three doubles 
teams won eight of nine matches. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy's David Schwartz won three of four at No. 1 singles, and No. 2 Bobby 
Butler swept his four opponents. Kennedy's Josh Etting and Che Naveja combined 
to win all three matches at No. 1 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy will face Dorsey on June 1 at the Racquet Centre for the City 3-A 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
In another tennis match: 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 10, Thousand Oaks 8 -- Beverly Hills outscored the Lancers, 4-2, 
in the last round of doubles matches to advance to the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Palmdale 3, Upland 1 -- Palmdale's Angie LePage struck out seven and walked 
none in a second-round Southern Section 3-A Division playoff game at Palmdale. 
</P>
<P>
Riverside Notre Dame 3, Alemany 2 (11 innings) -- Barrie Saavedra's single in 
the bottom of the 11th inning scored Glae Copeland in a Southern Section 2-A 
second-round playoff game. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Royal d. Pasadena Poly, 15-7, 15-7, 15-12 -- Top-seeded Royal advanced to the 
Southern Section 2-A Division final. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon d. Miraleste, 15-6, 15-13, 15-13 -- Kevin Sathre had 13 kills to lead 
Canyon (16-1) in a 2-A Division semifinal match. 
</P>
