<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEATTLE BANK TO USE ATMS TO DISPENSE STAMPS TO CLIENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From American Banker 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seattle-First National Bank will begin Saturday to dispense postage stamps at 
its automated teller machines -- a move that will spark increased interest in 
the future of ATMs as a source of products other than cash. 
</P>
<P>
If the highly touted joint venture between Seattle-First and the U.S. Postal 
Service proves successful, it may open doors for similar efforts across the 
country. 
</P>
<P>
Until now, banks and other institutions have made a variety of efforts to 
branch into products besides cash at ATMs. Products being tested include movie 
tickets, coupons, ski-lift tickets and other items that can be tailored to the 
size and thickness of currency. 
</P>
