<TEXT>
<P>
Helionetics Inc.: The Irvine manufacturer of power conditioning systems and 
other electronic equipment posted a loss of $638,000 for the first quarter, 
contrasted with earnings of $5.6 million for the comparable year-earlier 
period. 
</P>
<P>
The 1989 figure included an extraordinary gain of $5.5 million resulting from 
the company's reorganization plan. Revenue rose 47% to $2.2 million from $1.5 
million. 
</P>
<P>
Vincent P. Williams, president and chief executive, said the earnings loss 
resulted from insufficient liquidity to purchase certain parts and services 
needed to assemble and ship products, higher operating expenses and the cost of 
two acquisitions made during the second quarter of 1989. 
</P>
<P>
The improved revenue resulted from the contributions of the acquired firms. 
