<P>
COURTNEY PITCHES IN FOR TUSTIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TUSTIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bill Courtney pitched a five-hitter and struck out nine to lead Tustin High 
School to a 3-0 victory over Central in a Southern Section 3-A second-round 
playoff game Tuesday at Tustin. 
</P>
<P>
Courtney (7-0), a senior right-hander, retired 12 of the last 13 batters. 
</P>
<P>
He gave up a leadoff single to Roger Ray in the fourth, then retired 11 batters 
in a row before Ty Bilderback doubled with two outs in the seventh. He got 
Lenard Gomes to fly out to end the game. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin (24-3) scored a run in the first and two more in the second. Shawn Green 
had a two-run single in the second to put the Tillers ahead, 3-0. Ryan Relph 
had a two-out single to score Green in the first. Green started the first with 
a single, stole second and went to third on a groundout. 
</P>
<P>
Central had runners on second and third with one out in the third, but the 
runner on second was caught off base, and Courtney got a strikeout for the 
final out. Tustin plays La Quinta in the quarterfinals on Friday at a site to 
be determined. DALE RUHE 
</P>
