<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION TENNIS PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
CORONA DEL MAR WINS ON DOUBLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The doubles teams helped Corona del Mar High School beat host Loyola, 10-8, in 
a Southern Section 4-A second-round tennis match Tuesday at the South Pasadena 
Tennis Center. 
</P>
<P>
Ken Alston and Marshall Solomon, Corona del Mar's No. 1 doubles team, swept 
their sets, 6-0, 6-2, 6-0, and Scott Pannier and Trenton Rhodes, the Sea Kings' 
No. 2 team, swept, 6-3, 7-5, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar (22-2) will play Dana Hills, a 12-6 winner over Newport Harbor, 
in Thursday's semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
In 3-A matches: 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 15, Glendale 3 -- Top-seeded Woodbridge (20-3) advanced to the 
semifinals with an easy victory at home. Eric Berg, the Warriors' No. 1 singles 
player, swept his sets, 6-4, 6-2, 6-1. Darren Isaacman and Victory Ro, 
Woodbridge's No. 1 doubles team, swept their sets, 6-1, 6-0, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 10, Redlands 8 -- Host Laguna Beach got key victories from Julian 
Zajfen at No. 3 singles and Adam Donner and Jayson Tonkon at No. 3 doubles to 
take a 4-2 lead after the first round and held on to win. It was the first loss 
for Redlands (20-1). Jon Leach, Laguna Beach's No. 1 singles player, swept his 
sets, 6-1, 6-1, 6-0, to improve his record to 60-0 this season. 
</P>
<P>
In a 1-A match: 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita 12, Yucaipa 6 -- Sean Crafts swept his sets at No. 1 singles, 
6-4, 6-0, 6-0, to lead host Santa Margarita into the semifinals. Jeff Larson 
and Kevin Cimini, the Eagles' No. 1 doubles team, won two of three sets, 2-6, 
6-0, 7-5. Santa Margarita (16-3) plays Brentwood, a winner over Bellflower, 
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
