<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NOTES: KRONEMANN, LUBNER BEGIN PLAY TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC Irvine tennis players Trevor Kronemann and Richard Lubner will play 
first-round singles matches today in the NCAA Division I individual 
championships at the Grand Champions Resort in Indian Wells. 
</P>
<P>
Kronemann, who is ranked 20th in the nation and is a three-time All-American, 
will play No. 61 Mickey Maule of Southern Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
Lubner, ranked 33rd, will face No. 17 Michael Zimmerman of Harvard. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine's doubles team of Kronemann and Shige Kanroji, ranked 29th, begin play 
Thursday against the 12th-ranked team of Johan Donar and Conny Falk of Miami. 
</P>
<P>
Three former Orange County high school standouts were named to the all-Western 
Athletic Conference baseball team. 
</P>
<P>
Selected to the first team was Utah third baseman Mike Edwards, a former 
all-county defensive back at Valencia, and San Diego State designated 
hitter/catcher Eric Christopherson from Ocean View High School. 
</P>
</TEXT>
