<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wespercorp: The Irvine computer products company lost $46,000 for the third 
fiscal quarter ended March 31, compared to a net loss of $97,000 for the 
similar period last year. 
</P>
<P>
Sales declined 28%, to $342,000 from $476,000. For the nine-month period, the 
company posted net earnings of $2,000, contrasted with a year-earlier loss of 
$292,000. Sales fell 40%, to $1.2 million from nearly $2 million. The company 
said the sales decline for the nine-month period is attributed to the sale of 
its Audiofile product line, lower spare parts sales to the Federal Aviation 
Administration because of a supplier's delay in shipping material, and reduced 
sales of some products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
