<P>
BIKER IS CRITICAL AFTER CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Anaheim man was critically injured this morning when his speeding motorcycle 
plowed into a van on the Orange Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
John Sentino, 24, was traveling north near the Chapman Avenue off-ramp at 1:50 
a.m. at a speed estimated at more than 100 m.p.h. when he hit the van without 
applying his brakes, California Highway Patrol Officer Angel Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
At impact, he flipped off his motorcycle, flew about 40 feet and landed in the 
center divider, Johnson said. He was not wearing a helmet. No one in the van 
was injured. 
</P>
<P>
Sentino was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where he was listed in 
critical condition with massive head injuries and a broken leg, hospital 
spokeswoman Fran Tardiff said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
